-- Former Boxing Champ Tommy Morrison, Who Beat Foreman, Dies at 44
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2013-09-02T15:51:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-02/former-boxing-champ-tommy-morrison-who-beat-foreman-dies-at-44.html
Tommy Morrison, who defeated  George Foreman  to win the World Boxing Organization heavyweight title
and co-starred with Sylvester Stallone in the movie “Rocky V,”
has died, the Associated Press reported.  Morrison was 44. The AP quoted his manager, Tony Holden, as
saying the former boxer died last night at a hospital in Omaha,
Nebraska.  Morrison twice tested positive in 1996 for HIV. The AP said
today that Morrison’s family did not disclose the cause of
death.  Morrison had a career record of 48-3-1. He defeated former
champion Foreman in 1993 in a 12-round bout.  To contact the reporter on this story:
